Feature: Showing All books

As a User, I want to see all books
So that,   I can decide which book to borrow

@Valid
Scenario 1)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/books
WHEN  I make a Get Request
THEN  I should see all the books

Feature: Showing Specific book

As a User, I want to specific book
So that,   I can know its details

@Valid
Scenario 1)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/books/id
WHEN  I make a Get Request
THEN  I should see the requested book


Feature: ِAdding new Book

As a Library admin, I want to add new book
So that,   users can see it

@Valid
Scenario 1)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/books
WHEN  I make a Post Request
THEN  I should the book
AND   the book should be stored in the Book list

Feature: Deleting a Book

As a Library admin, I want to delete a book
So that,  I can remove any book uploaded by mistake

@Valid
Scenario 1)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/books/id
WHEN  I make a delete Request
THEN  the book should be removed from database (List)

Feature: Updating a Book

As a Library admin, I want to update a book
So that,  I can edit any mistakes in book details

@Valid
Scenario 1)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/books/id
WHEN  I make a Put Request
THEN  The updated book should be shown for me
AND   Stored in the database


Feature: Borrow a book

As a User , I want to borrow a book
So that,    I can read it

@Valid
Scenario 1)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/borrowRecord/bookID
WHEN  I make a Post Request
AND   I enter a valid book id
AND   I have < 5 borrowed books
AND   I don't have >= 3 overdue books
THEN  Create new Book Record
AND   Mark the book as borrowed

@Invalid
Scenario 2)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/borrowRecord/bookID
WHEN  I make a Post Request
AND   I enter a (non valid) book id
AND   I have < 5 borrowed books
AND   I don't have >= 3 overdue books
THEN  Refuse the request
AND   Show the user (The book is not available) message

@Invalid
Scenario 3)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/borrowRecord/bookID
WHEN  I make a Post Request
AND   I enter a valid book id
AND   I have >= 5 borrowed books
AND   I don't have >= 3 overdue books
THEN  Refuse the request
AND   Show the user (You can't borrow more that 5 books at a time) message

@Invalid
Scenario 4)
GIVEN I access http://localhost:5000/borrowRecord/bookID
WHEN  I make a Post Request
AND   I enter a valid book id
AND   I have < 5 borrowed books
AND   I have >= 3 overdue books
THEN  Refuse the request
AND   Show the user (You are blocked) message


Feature: Return a book

As a User , I want Return a book
So that,    I can read other books later

@Valid
Scenario 1)
GIVEN There is a book stored in database
WHEN  I borrow the book
AND   I try to return it
THEN  Set the return Date to current Date
AND   Update book availability to available
AND   Update the Record status to returned





